text: I hold my honey and I store my bread In little jars and cabinets of my will.
I label clearly, and each latch and lid I bid, Be firm till I return from Hell.

—GWENDOLYN BROOKS, Selected Poems

Stupid, stupid; Lily had been warned not to go to Haiti.
I warned her.
Why do people go to these places, these places that are not for them?
It must be that they believe in their night vision.
They believe themselves able to draw images up out of the dark.
But black wells only yield black water.
